# Reusable CSS Classes Reference

All classes below are defined in `src/index.css`. **Check these first** before writing Tailwind-only equivalents to keep the UI consistent.

---

## 1. Button Classes

### Base

| Class | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `.btn` | Base button — flex, font-weight 500, transition, rounded-lg (8px), focus ring |
| `.btn-primary` | Green bg `#136D6D`, white text, no border. Hover: `#0E5A5A` |
| `.btn-secondary` | `#FEFEFB` bg, `#072929` text, 1px `#e5e7eb` border. Hover: `#f5f5f0` |
| `.btn-outline` | Transparent bg, `#136D6D` text, 1px `#e5e7eb` border. Hover: `#f9fafb` |
| `.btn-ghost` | Transparent bg, `#072929` text, 1px `#e5e7eb` border. Hover: `#f9fafb` |

### Sizes

| Class | Padding | Font |
|-------|---------|------|
| `.btn-sm` | 6px 12px (overridden to `0.5rem 1rem !important` + `10.64px !important`) | 14px |
| `.btn-md` | 8px 16px | 16px |
| `.btn-lg` | 12px 24px | 18px |

### Specialized Buttons

| Class | Usage | Key Styles |
|-------|-------|------------|
| `.create-entity-button` | "Create Campaign", "Create Target", etc. | Green bg, white text, 40px height, 8px radius |
| `.edit-button` | Edit actions in data views | `#FEFEFB` bg, 40px height, 12px font, 8px radius |
| `.edit-button-large` | Larger edit buttons | White bg, 16px font, 500 weight |
| `.cancel-button` | Cancel/Clear actions | `#FEFEFB` bg, 40px height, `11.2px` font |
| `.apply-button` | Apply/Add Filter primary action | Green bg, white text, `11.2px` font |
| `.apply-button-add` | Add Filter variant | Green bg, 40px height, 10px/16px padding |
| `.add-button` | Small add buttons | Green bg, 8px/16px padding, `11.2px` font |
| `.assistant-prompt-button` | Suggested prompts in AI chat | White bg, border, full-width, left-aligned |

### Button Usage

```tsx
// Use CSS class for data-view buttons
<button className="create-entity-button">
  <Plus className="w-4 h-4" /> Create Campaign
</button>

// Use CSS class for edit/cancel in tables
<button className="edit-button">Edit</button>
<button className="cancel-button">Cancel</button>
<button className="apply-button">Apply</button>

// Use Tailwind or btn classes for custom buttons
<button className="btn btn-primary btn-md">Submit</button>
```

