## 10. AI Assistant Classes

The assistant panel uses 50+ CSS classes prefixed with `.assistant-*`. Key groups:

| Prefix | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `.assistant-top-row*` | Top tab bar (tabs, new chat, close) |
| `.assistant-tab-pill*` | Individual chat tab pills |
| `.assistant-account-row*` | Account/channel selector row |
| `.assistant-title-*` | Chat title row |
| `.assistant-message-content` | Message text styling (lists, paragraphs, tables) |
| `.assistant-table*` | Tables inside AI messages |
| `.assistant-thoughts-*` | Collapsible reasoning section |
| `.assistant-ran-tool-*` | Tool execution badges |
| `.assistant-history-*` | Chat history dropdown |
| `.assistant-setup-*` | Onboarding setup card (account/channel selection) |
| `.assistant-intent-badge` | Intent badge (analyze/create) |
| `.assistant-input-container` | Chat input bar |
| `.assistant-prompt-button` | Suggested prompt buttons |
| `.assistant-header-icon-btn` | Header action buttons |
| `.assistant-muted-text` | Loading/empty state text |

These classes use CSS custom properties (`var(--color-*)`, `var(--font-size-*)`) from the `@theme` block.

---

## Key Principles

1. **Check `index.css` first** — before writing inline Tailwind for tables, buttons, forms, or tabs
2. **Don't duplicate** — if a CSS class exists for the pattern, use it
3. **CSS classes for shared patterns** — tables, status badges, form inputs in data views
4. **Tailwind utilities for unique styling** — component-specific layout, spacing, responsive
5. **Combine both** — CSS class for base + Tailwind for overrides: `<button className="create-entity-button ml-auto">`
